   <note type="biographical/historical" displayLabel="Biographical Note">Henry Watkins Allen (1820-1866) established the Allendale sugar plantation in West Baton Rouge Parish, Louisiana, in the early 1850s. Allendale Plantation changed hands several times over the years, until 1882, when John and Martin James Kahao purchased the land, buildings, and equipment. The Kahao family successfully operated the plantation for most of the twentieth century, during which time it underwent a change in farming techniques, moving from hand labor and mule cultivation to mechanized farming.</note>
